    "20 (Box 1 and 2 in particular provides a succinct overview) and SRC 31 to be helpful for a more detailed step-by-step account of retrospective data harmonization protocols.",
    "Step 1 Preparatory stage.",
    "The chicken and egg aspect of data harmonization is especially pronounced in the preparatory phase.",
    "To begin with, the size and desired skill set for building a data harmonization team is to some extent dependent on how many datasets there are to harmonize and what kind of processing will need to be done in the implementation stage.",
    "Meanwhile the amount of funding that may be necessary to complete data harmonization can also be dependent on a number of factors, including the number of datasets involved, the necessity of purchasing dataset(s), the cost of storing or securing dataset(s), and the length of time and effort projected for harmonizing data during the implementation stage (which itself is a function of the quality and type of data desired for harmonization) 39."
  ]
